full_transcript: This is Prosper, and when we first spoke two years ago, he told me he used to think I was a cocky prick because I posted videos online. So when he asked me if I could help him start making content, I was like, bitch, only if you help teach me how to riz. So over the next six months, we'd hang out, we'd go cold approach half the time, and grind content the other half. And if I'm being completely honest, I always doubted Prosper, because content is hard. It's late nights, editing your video, making no money for months, all while putting yourself out there to be hated and cringed at. But if there's anything I've learned from being friends with Prosper now for two years, when you find a homie with an absolute dog inside him, and you spend enough time with them, life-changing shit happens. You're a good friend, aren't you? Yo, it's 9 a.m., and we've made $5,900. Nine fucking miles. So tomorrow, he's actually doing a live class breaking down how he grew 350,000 followers in a single year. So if you wanna learn how to build dog-like content discipline from the boyfriend maxer himself, comment diamond, and I'll send you the link to join that class. Yo, shout out to the people who understand that reference. Peace.
